prog_schedule.title: AnimeIowa Idol Fest
prog_schedule.description: A talented lineup of idol dance groups and individuals are ready to perform a variety of Japanese idol pop dances! Come cheer them on!

prog_schedule.title: Vocaloid At Home
prog_schedule.description: Have you ever wanted to go to Magical Mirai or any Vocaloid concert? We don't have the holograms, but we do have cosplayers! Come watch your favorite vocaloids perform some of our favorite songs as a concert for you!

prog_schedule.title: Cosplay for Spoonies
prog_schedule.panelists: Twilight Jasmine Cosplay and Prismatic Cosplay
prog_schedule.description: Cosplaying with chronic, mental, or invisible illnesses: time management, organization, accommodating mobility aides and medical devices.

prog_schedule.title: So you would like to be in the cosplay contest?
prog_schedule.description: Join us for this Q&A panel on AnimeIowa’s Cosplay Competition! Get information on how to compete and sign up for one of the remaining slots!

prog_schedule.title: Anime Alphabet
prog_schedule.description: Can you complete the entire alphabet with anime titles?  Walk through the alphabet with us, you may win a prize!  But be careful, others may know that anime too!

prog_schedule.title: Patterns and Pattern Alterations
prog_schedule.description: Having trouble finding or fitting a pattern for your cosplay? We have answers! We'll be covering an assortment of resources, pattern alteration, and fitting techniques to help build your patterning skills.

prog_schedule.title: Freya’s Protection: A Chain Mailing Journey
prog_schedule.description: Join Eleanor (Cutie PaBooty from Knights of the Round Pasties) as she shares about her chain mailing techniques, how she got into this unique art and history behind the art of chainmail.

prog_schedule.title: Six Degrees of Shinji Ikari
prog_schedule.description: The court is corrupt, the witnesses can lie, and the evidence doesn't exist! Put your debate skill and quick thinking to the test in this mock trial.

prog_schedule.title: Cosplay Consent
prog_schedule.description: Did you know that consent extends beyond intimate circumstances? Spreading the word of consent is a passion and mission of Celtic Honey.  Join in, as fae encourages you to participate in learning the types of consent and how best to navigate environments especially within the cosplay community.  Help spread the word of consent with a ribbon handed out the end that can be attached to your badge.  "Ask First!"

prog_schedule.title: Samurai Squid Games
prog_schedule.description: You thought the hit show was crazy? Come join Samurai Dan and try HIS version of the Squid Games! All ages appropriate.

prog_schedule.title: Fractured But Whole: Who will you decide?
prog_schedule.description: Have you wanted to be the greatest hero? Now is your chance to come prove who the greatest team is out there, what side will you choose?

prog_schedule.title: Iowa Pokemon League
prog_schedule.description: Seoulkat, BulbaDream, Broodmother, Nightstorm, Spirit, Str-Ogre, and DibtheAwesome. Do you think you are the very best? Well come try your luck against the Iowa Pokemon League! 8 gyms to face! Can you beat us all? S/V Ver. used.

prog_schedule.title: Drag it Up: A beginners guide to drag show etiquette, the art of drag, and more!
prog_schedule.panelists: Anna Mae, Sage Umbra, Emo Knievel, Kawaii Canary, Malaiya Marvel and Melee
prog_schedule.description: Explore the world of Drag with a host of experienced Drag Performers from all different spectrums who dive into the art of drag, the history of drag, drag show etiquette, finding your drag persona, body contouring, wig styling, makeup, and more!

prog_schedule.title: Iron Cosplay
prog_schedule.description: Teams will be challenged to create themed costumes using only the materials provided within the time limit, as well as adapt to twists along the way!

prog_schedule.title: Name That OST!
prog_schedule.description: OST (original soundtrack) has the power to tug at your heartstrings or hype you up. Join us as we play instrumental music from anime, games and cartoons and allow attendees to guess their source. There will be prizes for winners! At the end of the panel we'll open up sharing and discussion of our favorite pieces.

prog_schedule.title: Ouran You Glad the Host Club is Here?
prog_schedule.panelists: Ouran You Glad the Host Club is Here?
prog_schedule.description: Come join the host club yet again at AnimeIowa! Come watch the hosts of Ouran Highschool's host club guess commonfolk slang and phrases.

prog_schedule.title: Ball Jointed Dolls Intro and Meetup
prog_schedule.description: Ever wonder about the dolls you sometimes see people carrying at the convention or collect dolls and want to meet up with others in the hobby? The main focus will be on resin ball jointed dolls, but other types of dolls are also welcome!

prog_schedule.title: Samurai Sword Class
prog_schedule.description: Actual Samurai battlefield techniques, taught by a professional swordsman. Weapons (bokken) provided.

prog_schedule.title: Anime Name That Tune
prog_schedule.panelists: Avant-Garden Cosplay and Blushing Violet Cosplay
prog_schedule.description: Test your anime tune skills in this tournament-style competition! Audience members can play along too, no knowledge needed!

prog_schedule.title: The Samurai battlefield in the Sengoku era
prog_schedule.description: We will discuss the realities of the battlefield for the samurai including communication, weapons!

prog_schedule.title: Fate Grand Order! Let's go!
prog_schedule.description: A dive into the obsession, character development, historical inaccuracy, gameplay, AND MEMES we can make together! Unofficial fan run panel.

prog_schedule.title: Annamaniacs
prog_schedule.panelists: Hosted and MC'd by Anna Mae, starring: Sage Umbra, Emo Knievel, Kawaii Canary, Malaiya Marvel and Melee
prog_schedule.description: Join the maniacs of Cirque du Buque for one night only!  Drag artists from across the Midwest come together to share their penchant for the darkness with cosplay and horror themed acts stretching from anime to cult classics.  Kings, queens, and non-binary things, we've got a little something for everyone!

prog_schedule.title: Anime Anatomy
prog_schedule.description: Just what would it take for humans to evolve cat ears? We’ll tell you if your fave character is valid from a scientific viewpoint.

prog_schedule.title: History of Horror
prog_schedule.description: Join horror expert Semetary Cosplay and travel down the world of vampires, werewolves, slashers, and more in this educational panel of how certain horror genres got started, best horrors to watch for those just wanting to dip their toes into the genre, and delve into the world of horror cosplay.

prog_schedule.title: How to Incorporate Kimono into Cosplay
prog_schedule.panelists: Tangerine Mountain: Tiffany Erickson and Lisa Truong
prog_schedule.description: Join Tangerine Mountain for an in-depth discussion about kimono and the role it can have in cosplay!  We will cover topics such as how to cosplay responsibly while being culturally sensitive; cultural exchange vs. cultural appropriation as it pertains to representing popular characters utilizing kimono; and use examples of creative ways of bringing characters to life from presenters Tiffany Erickson and Lisa Troung’s experiences modeling and participating in the World Cosplay Summit. Bring your cosplay ideas to further the discussion.

prog_schedule.title: Knights of the Round Pasties’ Buu-lesque!
prog_schedule.panelists: Absassin, Eden Draconis, Princess Slaya, Luna Macaroon, M'Lady Rae, and Largo Lyrical
prog_schedule.description: Stage Kittens: Cutie Pa Booty, Thunder, All Hallows Eve, and Short Stacked King (Muscles). The Knights bring Buu’s Boos and Baes to the stage! But wait, There’s MORE!! In a steamy mash up the Knights have teamed up with Naughty Nerds Cabaret to bring you an evening of Naughty Nerdom and Monsters that go Bump and Grind in the night!!

prog_schedule.title: I'm So Dumb 18+
prog_schedule.description: Life lessons don’t come easy to Samurai Dan. Hear him relive his most traumatic con moments during his stand up show.

prog_schedule.title: Let's talk about mature comics
prog_schedule.description: Discuss favorite adult webcomics, seinen manga, yaoi/yuri and anything nsfw comics. Come with recommendations.

prog_schedule.title: You Don't Know Japan 18+
prog_schedule.description: Think you know Japan? Think again! We'll explore the crazy wild side of our neighbors to the East in this trivia based game show. IYKYK.

prog_schedule.title: Sexiest Characters of Anime
prog_schedule.description: Ever wanted to see a live show from the hottest characters of your favorite animes? Well now you can! We have a line up you'll never forget!

prog_schedule.title: NO! V: The Final Frontier
prog_schedule.description: Comedy-improv gameshow where the contestants vie for prizes, but if they lose they go to the audience. Hilarity ensues.

prog_schedule.title: The Best of AO3 tags
prog_schedule.description: Join us as we talk about our favorite AO3 tags and rate them! Feel free to bring your own. This will be an hour of just giggles and pure chaos, maybe choking.

prog_schedule.title: Shin Kangaroo Saiban - Zero Justice
prog_schedule.description: The court is corrupt, the witnesses can lie, and the evidence doesn't exist! Put your debate skill and quick thinking to the test in this mock trial.

prog_schedule.title: Doujin Mad Libs
prog_schedule.description: Help us create some truly terrible doujin translations. We’ve blocked out some choice words from several doujins to be filled in by the audience and presented.

prog_schedule.title: Cosplay Contest Orientation
prog_schedule.description: *Closed to Cosplay Masquerade participants* Mandatory orientation for those competing in Saturday night's cosplay contest! No need to come in costume unless you want to test your shoes or a prop on the stage. Please show up promptly! Cosplay staff will be going over the agenda for the show and any last minute questions from contestants.

prog_schedule.title: Sports Anime Stretch Hour
prog_schedule.description: Sore from having too much fun at the con? Stretch your muscles with some floor stretches and light exercises from some favorite sports anime.

prog_schedule.title: Crossplay and Genderbend 101
prog_schedule.description: Join Semetary Cosplay as he teaches the art of perfecting the skill of the crossplay and genderbending world. Tips such as safe binding, makeup skills, and getting the right palette to represent the character that you want to bring to life will be presented in this informative educational panel.

prog_schedule.title: Anime Game Show Explosion
prog_schedule.description: We're back with more trivia, more prizes, moar shenanigans, and more free pocky than you can shake a shojo mallet at!

prog_schedule.title: No Means No Self Defense Class
prog_schedule.description: People have a right to personal space and safety. This self defense class teaches easy to use concepts and techniques to ensure those rights.

prog_schedule.title: Avatar: Kung Fu Elements
prog_schedule.description: Join Korra on an adventure through the Kung Fu styles that inspired the elements in Avatar: The Last Airbender! As a practitioner of Kung Fu for well over a decade, see two of the styles (water and air) in demonstration form and learn some moves to show your friends! A beginner course into the mechanics behind the internal fighting arts. We'll touch on all four inspirations behind the styles of earth, fire, water and air. You will also learn basics that translate to easy self defense as well as philosophies in life.

prog_schedule.title: Positivity Speed Dating
prog_schedule.description: (Limit 24 People, please show up early for panel if you want to get in!) Let's take the concept of speed 'dating', but make it....speed positivity! Join moderator Semetary Cosplay as you meet new friends and individuals and spend the next hour building people up through the power of compliments and create confidence! Notebooks and pens will be provided to every participant, that way you will have your own confidence notebook to bring home at the end of the panel.

prog_schedule.title: AnimeIowa’s Dance Party and Light Show
prog_schedule.description: Come out and shake it to some of AnimeIowa’s favorite tunes! Party starts at 10pm, don’t be late.
